# Standard Node + tooling artefacts.
node_modules
dist
coverage
.nyc_output
*.tsbuildinfo
*.log
.DS_Store

# Real-world env strategy:
#   - `.env`              committed (no secrets; shared base)
#   - `.env.<mode>`       committed (non-secret per-env hostnames, etc.)
#   - `.env.local`        gitignored (per-developer override on YOUR machine)
#   - `.env.<mode>.local` gitignored (per-developer + per-mode override)
#
# Production secrets are NEVER committed — they arrive from Vault /
# K8s Secret / Doppler / GitHub Actions secrets at deploy time and
# win over file values via the cascade.
#
# (In the @env-kit/node-settings repo itself, the parent .gitignore
# exempts everything under sample/ so the example stays readable —
# this file documents what your *real* project's .gitignore should
# look like.)
.env.local
.env.*.local
